Data Deletion Instructions for Photo Grid
Last Updated: February 1, 2026
Overview
At Photo Grid (Klein Industries), we respect your privacy rights and provide you with multiple ways to delete your personal data from our systems. This document outlines the step-by-step process for requesting data deletion.

Your Data Deletion Rights
Under various privacy laws including the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) and the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), you have the right to request deletion of your personal information that Photo Grid has collected about you.
Upon receipt of a valid data deletion request, we will:

Delete your account and associated profile information
Remove cached copies of your Instagram posts and metadata
Delete your usage data and preferences
Remove you from our marketing communications
Confirm deletion within 45 days (or as required by law)


How to Request Data Deletion
Option 1: Email Request (Recommended)
Send a data deletion request email to:
lineupmusicandsound@gmail.com
Email Subject Line: "Data Deletion Request for Photo Grid"
Include in your email:

Your full name
Your email address associated with your Photo Grid account
Your Instagram business account username (if applicable)
Statement: "I request deletion of all personal data associated with my Photo Grid account"
Your preferred confirmation method (email)

Example:
Subject: Data Deletion Request for Photo Grid

Dear Photo Grid Support,

I am requesting the deletion of all personal data associated with my account.

Account Details:
- Name: [Your Full Name]
- Email: [Your Email Address]
- Instagram Username: [Your Instagram Handle]

Please delete all information Photo Grid has collected about me and confirm completion of this request.

Thank you,
[Your Name]
Option 2: In-App Deletion (If Available)
If Photo Grid provides an in-app account deletion feature:

Log into your Photo Grid account
Navigate to Settings > Privacy & Account
Select "Delete My Account"
Follow the on-screen prompts
Confirm the deletion request
You will receive a confirmation email

Option 3: Instagram Revocation
You can immediately revoke Photo Grid's access to your Instagram data by:

Go to your Instagram account settings
Navigate to Apps and Websites
Find "Photo Grid" in the connected apps list
Click on Photo Grid
Select "Remove"
Confirm the disconnection

Note: This immediately prevents Photo Grid from accessing new data, but previously cached data may require a formal deletion request via email for complete removal.

What Data Gets Deleted
Upon processing your data deletion request, we will delete:
Account Data

Your account username and email address
Account creation date and login history
Account preferences and settings
Password and authentication credentials

Instagram Data

Cached copies of Instagram posts you authorized us to pull
Post metadata (captions, timestamps, engagement metrics)
Images and videos associated with cached posts
Audience insights or performance data

Usage Data

Your interaction history with the Photo Grid app
Features you accessed and when
Device information associated with your account
IP addresses and cookies linked to your account

Communications Data

Marketing emails and promotional communications
Support correspondence related to your account


Data We May Retain
In limited circumstances, we may retain certain information:
Legal and Compliance Requirements

Data retained to comply with laws or regulations (e.g., tax records)
Data needed for legal defense or disputes
Data required by government agencies or law enforcement
We will retain such data only as long as legally required

Aggregated and Anonymous Data

We may retain aggregated, anonymized data that cannot identify you
This data cannot be traced back to your account

Backup Copies

Data in automated backup systems may take up to 90 days to fully delete
These backups are isolated and not accessible for normal operations


Verification of Deletion Request
When you submit a data deletion request, we will:

Acknowledge receipt within 5 business days via email
Verify your identity by requesting additional information if needed
Process your request within 45 days (or as required by applicable law)
Confirm completion with a deletion confirmation email
Provide additional details about any data we retained due to legal requirements

Identity Verification
To prevent unauthorized deletion requests, we may ask you to:

Confirm your email address or phone number
Answer security questions you set up
Verify ownership of your Instagram business account
Provide other proof of identity


Processing Timeline

Email Received: Day 0
Acknowledgment Email Sent: Within 5 business days
Processing Period: Within 45 days of verified request
Confirmation Email Sent: Within 45 days of processing completion

You will receive an email confirmation when your data has been deleted.

Special Circumstances
If You Are a California Resident (CCPA)
California law requires us to:

Acknowledge your request within 45 days
Provide specific information about the data we collect
Delete data unless an exception applies
Not discriminate against you for exercising your rights

You also have the right to:

Know what personal information is collected
Know whether personal information is sold or disclosed
Delete personal information collected from you
Opt-out of the sale or sharing of your personal information

If You Are in the European Union (GDPR)
Under GDPR, you have the right to:

Request erasure of your data ("right to be forgotten")
Have your request processed within 30 days
Appeal to a supervisory authority if we deny your request
Request proof of deletion


Frequently Asked Questions
Q: Will deleting my account delete my posts from Instagram?
A: No. Photo Grid only deletes cached copies of your posts from our servers. Your original posts remain on Instagram. To delete Instagram posts, you must delete them directly from Instagram.
Q: How long does deletion take?
A: We aim to process deletion requests within 45 days. You'll receive a confirmation email when completed.
Q: Can I recover my data after deletion?
A: Once deleted, your data cannot be recovered. Please ensure you want to delete your information before submitting a request.
Q: What if I submit a request but don't receive confirmation?
A: Check your spam/junk folder. If you still don't receive acknowledgment within 7 days, contact us directly.
Q: Can I request deletion of only specific data?
A: You can specify which data you'd like deleted in your email. We will delete what's possible while retaining legally required data.
Q: What if my deletion request is denied?
A: We will explain why in our response email. You have the right to appeal or contact a privacy regulator.

Need Help?
If you have questions about the data deletion process or need assistance:
Contact Us:
Email: lineupmusicandsound@gmail.com
In your email, please include:

Your account email
Description of your issue
Any previous deletion request reference numbers

We will respond to your inquiry within 5 business days.

Deletion Request Email Template
You can copy and use this template:

To: lineupmusicandsound@gmail.com
Subject: Data Deletion Request for Photo Grid
Dear Photo Grid Privacy Team,
I am submitting a formal request for deletion of all personal data associated with my Photo Grid account as permitted under applicable privacy laws including CCPA and GDPR.
Account Information:

Full Name: [Your Name]
Email Address: [Your Email]
Instagram Business Account Username: [Your Instagram Handle]
Date Account Created (if known): [Date]

Request Details:
I request the complete deletion of all personal information Photo Grid has collected, used, or stored about me, including but not limited to:

My account profile information
Cached Instagram posts and metadata
Usage data and interaction history
Cookies and device identifiers
Any other personal information

Please confirm completion of this deletion request via email.
Thank you,
[Your Full Name]
[Your Phone Number (optional)]

